{"artefact":[["_response_info",{"status":"ok"}],["title","Apprenticeships"],["id","https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/apprenticeships.json"],["web_url","https://www.gov.uk/apprenticeships"],["format","answer"],["details",{"need_id":"303","business_proposition":false,"alternative_title":"","overview":"Apprenticeships combine training on the job and studying towards a qualification - who can apply, pay, benefits","updated_at":"2012-10-08T17:02:00+00:00","body":"\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>Apprenticeships combine practical training on the job and studying towards a qualification.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>How do apprenticeships work?</h2>\n\n<p>Companies hire apprentices as employees and get them trained up by qualified professionals. Usually for 1 day a week, apprentices go to school to study towards a qualification.</p>\n\n<p>Anyone in England over 16 and not in full-time education can apply for an apprenticeship.</p>\n\n<p>Apprenticeships generally take between 2 and 4 years.</p>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://apprenticeshipvacancymatchingservice.lsc.gov.uk/navms/Forms/Candidate/Apprenticeships.aspx\" title=\"search apprenticeships\">Search apprenticeships</a>  </p>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.apprenticeships.org.uk/Types-of-Apprenticeships.aspx\" title=\"types of apprenticeships\">Types of apprenticeships</a></p>\n\n<h2>Levels of apprenticeships</h2>\n\n<p>There are 3 levels:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Intermediate \u2013 equivalent to 5 GCSE passes </li>\n  <li>Advanced \u2013 equivalent to 2 A level passes </li>\n  <li>Higher Apprenticeships \u2013 lead to NVQ Level 4 or Foundation Degree</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Pay and holidays</h2>\n\n<p>The minimum wage for apprentices is \u00a32.60 per hour but many earn more. On average apprentices earn \u00a3170 per week.</p>\n\n<p>Apprentices get at least 20 days of holidays per year, plus bank holidays.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Talk to a career adviser about apprenticeships on 0800 100 900.</p>\n</div>\n\n"}],["tags",[{"title":"Recruiting and hiring","id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/tags/employing-people%2Frecruiting-hiring.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes discrimination law, apprenticeships and using agencies","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Frecruiting-hiring","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/recruiting-hiring"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/tags/employing-people.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes pay, contracts and hiring","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Finding a job","id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/tags/working%2Ffinding-job.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes job search, volunteering, apprenticeships and job offers","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/with_tag.json?tag=working%2Ffinding-job","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working/finding-job"},"parent":{"title":"Working, jobs and pensions","id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/tags/working.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes holidays and finding a job","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/with_tag.json?tag=working","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working"},"parent":null}}]],["related",[{"title":"National Minimum Wage rates","id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/national-minimum-wage-rates.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/national-minimum-wage-rates","format":"answer","details":{"need_id":"1859","business_proposition":false}},{"title":"Apply for an apprenticeship","id":"https: